= ruby-flickr

PLEASE NOTE: BE SURE TO UNINSTALL RFLICKR BEFORE USING RUBY-FLICKR ... IT WILL CONFLICT

== Getting Started

You need to first get an API key as detailed here:

http://www.flickr.com/services/api/misc.api_keys.html

== Example

require 'flickr'

flickr = Flickr.new('YOUR_API_KEY')

photos = flickr.photos.search(:tags => 'traingo', :per_page => 10)
puts photos.inspect
puts photos.next_page.inspect
puts photos.previous_page.inspect

while photos = photos.next_page
  puts photos.page
end